      <Subject>Re: General Rule - Do not forbid - only guide except for safety</Subject>
      <Text>
        <Sent id="3.1">I think even WCAG 1.0 can be regarded as consistent with this method of </Sent>
        <Sent id="3.2">specifying guidelines, in that the word &amp;quot;avoid&amp;quot; was deliberately chosen to </Sent>
        <Sent id="3.3">imply the existence of alternative, more accessible, means of achieving </Sent>
        <Sent id="3.4">the same objective. WCAG 2.0 should, however, make this point clearer, to </Sent>
        <Sent id="3.5">avoid (pun intended) giving the impression that there are prohibitions in </Sent>
        <Sent id="3.6">the guidelines that would limit the capacity of content creators to design </Sent>
        <Sent id="3.7">web sites that fulfill their respective purposes.</Sent>
      </Text>
